# Docusaurus Configuration Guide

This project is a Docusaurus documentation site for the Don't Starve Together Vanilla API.

## Key Configuration Files

- [docusaurus.config.ts](mdc:dst-api-webdocs/docusaurus.config.ts) - Main configuration file that defines site settings, plugins, and theme options
- [sidebars.ts](mdc:dst-api-webdocs/sidebars.ts) - Defines the sidebar navigation structure for documentation
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:dst-api-webdocs/tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration

## Important Directories

- `/docs` - Contains markdown documentation files
- `/src/pages` - Contains React components for custom pages
- `/static` - Static assets like images and the 404 page

## GitHub Pages Deployment

This site is configured for deployment on GitHub Pages with the following settings:

- Base URL: `/dst-api-webdocs/`
- Organization: `vietnd69`
- Project: `dst-api-webdocs`

## Routing and Redirects

The site uses client-side redirects to handle navigation:

- The homepage redirects to the documentation using relative paths
- The 404 page has special handling for GitHub Pages
- All links in the site should use relative paths (without the baseUrl) as Docusaurus will automatically add the baseUrl in production

